Three hosts in two domains are connected through five routers.

The router fhrouter1 uses iptables drop mechanism

the rules are
iptables [options]
Valid options 
-A INPUT|OUTPUT (filter the packet in the input or at the output)
-s ipAddress/mask (example -s 192.168.1.1/32) filter packets with source address ipAddress  
-d ipAddress/mask (example -d 192.168.1.1/32) filter packets with destination address ipAddress
-p udp|tcp  filtered protocol.
-sport port protocol port filtered, source port 
-dport port (example filter http -dport 80)protocol port filtered, destination port 
-i interface filter packets that uses this interface
-j rule, only support DROP in this moment  